  "prompt": "Why was I blocked from adding questions on quora anonymously and how can I change it?",
  "response": "If you were blocked from asking questions anonymously on Quora, it could be due to a few reasons:\n\n1. **Violation of Guidelines**: You may have violated Quora's content guidelines or community standards, which can lead to restrictions on your ability to post anonymously.\n\n2. **Spam or Abuse Reports**: If your previous questions or contributions have been flagged by other users as spam or abusive, this could result in a temporary or permanent block on anonymous questions.\n\n3. **Account Limitations**: New accounts or accounts with low activity may have more restrictions placed on them until they build a history of positive contributions.\n\nTo change this and regain the ability to ask questions anonymously, you can try the following steps:\n\n1. **Review Quora\u2019s Policies**: Familiarize yourself with Quora's content guidelines and community standards to ensure your future contributions comply with their rules.\n\n2. **Check for Notifications**: Look for any emails or notifications from Quora regarding the block. Sometimes they provide information about why certain actions were taken on your account.\n\n3. **Reach Out to Quora Support**: If you believe the block was a mistake, you can reach out to Quora\u2019s support team. Provide as much detail as possible and ask for clarification or reconsideration of your case.\n\n4. **Contribute Positively**: Focus on contributing positively to the community with quality answers and questions. This may help lift any restrictions based on your overall account behavior.\n\n5. **Be Patient**: Sometimes, restrictions may be temporary. If you\u2019ve recently started receiving penalties, showing good behavior over time might allow you to regain full functionality.\n\nRemember that rules and systems can change, so it's always best to refer to Quora\u2019s help center for the latest information.",
